      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <p><lb n="1"/>catus-samudrātikkrānta-kīrttiḥ pratāpānurāgopanatānya-rāj<choice>
            <sic>ā</sic>
            <corr>o</corr>
          </choice>
varṇṇāśrama-vyavastḥĀpana-pravr̥tta<lb break="no" n="2"/>-cakkraś cakkradhara Iva prajānām artti-haraḥ śrī-mah<unclear>ā</unclear>rāja-harivarmm<unclear>ā</unclear> tasya puttras tat-pādānuddhyāto ja<lb break="no" n="3"/>yasvāminī-bhaṭṭārikā-devyām utpannaḥ
śrī-mahārājādityavarmmā tasya puttras tat-pādānuddhyāto <sic>jayasvāminī</sic><lb break="no" n="4"/>-bhaṭṭārikā-devyām utpannaḥ śrī-mahārājeśvaravarmmā tasya puttras tat-pādānuddhyāta Upaguptā-bhaṭṭārikā<lb break="no" n="5"/>-devyām utpanno mahārājādhirāja-śrī-īśāna-varmmā tasya puttras tat-pādānuddhyāto <lb n="6"/>lakṣmīvatī-bhaṭṭārikā-mahādevyām utpanno mahārājādhirāja-śrī-śarvvavarmmā <lb n="7"/>tasya puttras tatpādānuddhyāta <unclear>indra</unclear>-bhaṭṭārikā-mahādevyām utpanna<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> parama-māheśvaro <lb n="8"/>mahārājādhirāja-śrī-<unclear>avantivarmmā</unclear> maukhariḥ<!--
Note the repetition of the name Jayasvāminī in l3; the mother of Īśvaravarman should be Harṣaguptā. Probably a scribal mistake.
--><!--
Vats notes that the last two lines are badly worn throughout, and that the name of Avantivarmmā is "quite distinct" in the original even though it is quite illegible in the photograph.
--></p>
